neutrino.2307.16229:
2023-07-30, **On ultrahigh-energy neutrino-nucleon deep-inelastic scattering and the Froissart bound**, A. V. Kotikov et.al., [2307.16229v1](http://arxiv.org/abs/2307.16229v1)

 A brief review of the results for the total cross section \sigma^{
u N} of ultrahigh-energy neutrino deep inelastic scattering on isoscalar nuclear targets is presented. These results are based on simple approximations for \sigma^{
u N} and are compared with the experimental data of the IceCube Collaboration. The total cross section \sigma^{
u N} is proportional to the structure function F\_2^{
u N}(M\_V^2/s,M\_V^2), where M\_V is the intermediate boson mass and s is square of the energy of the center of mass. The coefficient in the front of F\_2^{
u N}(M\_V^2/s,M\_V^2) depends on the asymptotic behavior of F\_2^{
u N} at low values of x. It contains an additional term \sim \ln{s} if F\_2^{
u N} is scaled by the power \ln(1/x). Therefore, the asymptotic behavior of F\_2^{
u N}\propto\ln^2(1/x) for small x often assumed in the literature already leads to violation of the Froissart bound for \sigma^{
u N}.
